Newly appointed International Pentecost Holiness Church (IPHC) Comforter Michael Sandlana has filed a R2m defamation lawsuit against Alex FM and its talk show presenters for claiming that he was facing criminal charges. Sandlana, who was appointed IPHC leader by the executive committee despite a pending legal battle over the leadership of the church, filed court papers at the high court in Joburg demanding that the community radio station retract statements made against him during one of the station's talk shows presented by Muntu Mabunjwa and someone identified in papers only as a Mr Msiza. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD